2A. (1) The legal aid services given under this Act shall consist of
the following:
(a) legal aid in criminal cases as provided in Part III;
(b) legal aid in civil actions as provided in Part IV;
(c) legal advice as provided in Part V;
(d) mediation services as provided in Part VA; and
(e) legal companion services as provided in Part VB.
(2) The legal aid services referred to in subsection (1) may be given
to the citizens of Malaysia only.
